And sure, you might say, it’s my choice. I’m lucky to be able to work from home. I truly am! I’m not denying that. But think about the people who can’t. Shouldn’t they have that option? They don’t, because some dumbass out there needs McNuggets right now
And I’ve fiddled with medications and vitamins and sleeping schedules and time off but the fact of the matter is at some point I’ve done everything I can do to function and YET

And I know that those of us who have been cautious have saved lives that we don’t know about just as the careless have killed people they don’t know about. And I know that life isn’t fair. But I’m exhausted and I don’t have the ability to replenish myself.

But fucking get it right, nobody’s scared any more. We are angry. We are sick of your shit. Because we have been acting responsibly this whole time and some of us have gotten sick and died even after bending over backwards to keep your stupid asses safe
And it would be so easy to just step out. To just say “fuck it I’m just gonna go out and do what I want.” To be one of those people jeering “you can’t hide inside and live in fear forever!”

And, the longer it goes on like this, the longer it will take to resolve, so the longer those of us opting for safety and care are stuck following rules and making sacrifices and watching other people cough on each other’s eyeballs for fun and going on the vacations we cancelled

It’s not even that I think people shouldn’t have the freedom and agency to decide what to do with themselves (though this past year has definitely given me opinions) it’s the fact that our infrastructure is not set up to support people opting to safely withdraw.
I’m so angry and frustrated that people are going about their lives and spreading this fucking disease, which they have the choice to do, but I don’t have the choice to not engage with them.

COVID’s silver lining is that everyone is realizing that. People with chronic pain, or mental health conditions, are seeing things manifest in others that they could only previously describe. Our invisible agonies are becoming unable to be ignored.

And it’s not just me. The things I lived through weren’t big traumatic events. They were small inconveniences, personality traits. This has taught me that goddamn everyone is broken and defective. And society is built for the perfect.

Yeah, I’m broken and defective. But I’ve learned a lot through my therapy. I’ve learned that part of my issues came from a minor physical disability, and part came from a lifetime of being high stress. Cortisol messes everything else up, you guys.

Now I’m seeing other people functioning and am like “hey they’re having a Good Spoon Day! Good on them!” And I’m reasonably sure they’re tired too. And that they have days they spend in bed. And that I’m certainly, definitely, not the broken and defective one.

For one thing COVID has really shined a spotlight on how everyone is Not Okay. I appreciate that. Even when I’m okay, I know I’m Not Okay. Hormones, mental chemicals, fatigue, stress. But instead of seeing other people functioning and feeling guilty, I’m seeing things differently

I’m very tired.

K goes to the bathroom. I finish my review. A scoops up C and gives her some coloring. I am tired and full of Feelings. K comes out of the bathroom and I assure her that she didn’t do anything wrong and I’m not mad at her. We hug. Dinner is somen. Kids are happy. I’m tired. END

I YELL AT K TO GO TO HER ROOM SO C’S SCREAMING DOESNT MAKE HER LOSE HER MIND. SHE SCREAMS MORE. I SCREAM. SHE SCREAMS. CECE SCREAMS. K SCREAMS THAT SHE HAS TO GO TO THE BATHROOM AND WE SCREAM TO JUST GO THEN

WITH MY THUMBS. SO IT TOOK THREE TIMES AS LONG. K IS STANDING IN THE MIDDLE OF THE FLOOR HAVING A SCREAMING BREAKDOWN WITH HER HANDS OVER HER EARS. C IS CLIMBING ON ME SCREAMING. I CANT RETURN THE FIGURES BECAUSE THEY HAVE BEEN SEEM. I AM FURIOUS BEYOND REASON.

I IMMEDIATELY OPENED AMAZON APP AND WROTE A SCATHING REVIEW. C HAD SEEN THE FIGURES AND BEGAN PLEADING FOR THEM, THEN SCREAMING. K BEGINS TO SCREAM AND CRY BECAUSE C IS SCREAMING. TWO GIRLS SCREAMING AND CRYING AND CLIMBING ON ME WHILE I TRY TO TYPE A FURIOUS REVIEW.
I LOST MY SHIT.

I was very careful when I ordered these to make sure I was getting the good kind. I double checked, looked at the product photos. I paid extra to get the good ones. The hollow ones were 10, the good ones 18. Worth it!

I opened the package. They were the hollow ones.

The Amazon package I got for C has arrived! She loves the Sesame Street figures my mom got for her so I got her the other set. There are two types, the heavy well made Playskool kind and the hollow cheap Hasbro kind. They look almost the same, but are slightly different.

Mildly annoyed at the way my day has gone, I laugh to myself and think, haha, well, God is good anyway. Whatever. It’s fine. I get home and stand outside the door for 10 minutes trying to dig out my keys with my hands full. Okay. Get in the door and drop my keys, haha.

He finally leaves. I go into the meeting. One hour meeting takes two. A thunderstorm rages outside. Makes it hard to concentrate on the meeting which is all in Japanese. Oh well. Meeting is over. Realize I forgot an errand I’d been forgetting all day. Welp. Haha.

I entered the Skype meeting and the office doorbell goes off. It’s the guy with the delivery. He will not leave. He will not shut up. I end up having to deal with him for about 15 minutes while my supervisors in Japan wonder why I’m not talking and I desperately hope I’m muted.

Back to the office, was a little late. Oh well. Got some more things done. Printer jam. Oh well, fixed it. Something was going to be delivered and I just wanted to get that, then I could go home. Realized at about 15 min to 5 that I had a Skype meeting at 5 I forgot about. Haha.

None of it was there. None of it. None of those things, at the craft store or Target. Cafe was closed. Entire lunch break was spent searching, got nothing I needed, and ran out of time to get lunch. Had a minor panic attack in Target. Lol, it happens. Oh well.

Wanted to run a couple errands at the craft store and Target. Wanted to get - some cute face masks, some elastic roll, an automatic handheld little stitcher, maybe some fabric markers, some specialty gummies they usually sell, and get lunch at the Target Cafe to take to office.

Anyway. Went into the office. Got some work done. Realized I forgot my company card at home and had to order some components on my personal card. It’s fine. Whatever. I’ll just get paid back and have to make sure I remember to get an expense report done and then pay the balance.

This week I’ve been having to go into the office. That’s fine. Yesterday I found out the AC compressor in my car is dead and it’ll cost $700 to fix. It’s fine. That’s a good price for fixing it. $700 just sucks anyway.

I have a rant in me and this is essentially the only place I feel comfortable hashing it out so here we go. NOTE: I don’t need problem solving. My job is problem solving. I need to have feelings right now so here come feelings. This rant is about TODAY.

@kinomatika So at least it goes both ways. Just make sure you factor in escrow (take the average yearly taxes for the house, you can usually get the history, divide by 12 and add to payment) and PMI if you have it (~$40) when you’re estimating your monthly mortgage payment.

@kinomatika So sometimes they’re like “hey if you keep this same payment amount your escrow fund is gonna be short so your monthly payment is going to be more. ONCE (I bought our house...3 years ago? I think?) they were like “WE MESSED UP TAX WAS WAY LESS HERES A CHECK”

@kinomatika ^pays it for you and charges you for it throughout the year instead of being like “winter taxes time $2000 now pls”. The problem is that they charge the payments in advance and estimate what tax will be to decide what the payments are going to be. (Cont 3)

@kinomatika You don’t have to pay PMI if you have the 20% down payment on the house right away, otherwise you have to pay it every month until you get to 20% equity on the loan. That’s usually about $40/mo? And property taxes come due twice a year. The mortgage company pays it (cont. 2)

@kinomatika I’ll try! I don’t get it completely but I at least read the escrow statements when they come. Escrow is the amount that your mortgage company slaps on top of your monthly payment to cover property taxes (since they pay those for you) and PMI (private mortgage insurance) (cont.)

@kinomatika Just be careful because mortgage payments can change because of escrow, mortgage insurance, etc. my mortgage on my house went from ~700 to ~1000/month because the lender was like “OOPS we weren’t charging you enough escrow haha  ¯\_(ツ)_/¯”
